item.title: C4D help
item.dc:creator: @SomethingToHide STH
item.description:
@SomethingToHide wrote:

Seriously though, not trying to discourage you, take that guitar off your todo list.

I’ve been modeling for a WHILE, and it’s still kinda a challenge to model a guitar. I still have mistakes, and I still have to think about how I’m going to do somethings.

Honestly, if you can’t even do this simple stuff, or even buy Cinema4D, you need a LOTTTT more experience.

I’m tired of all these new people trying humongous feats. I’m serious too. You want to make something you’re proud of, not some peice of shit that’s horrible to look at, and people tell you ways to improve.

I’d much rather make something great, and have people critique it, than make something shitty and have people critique it, don’t you think?

Read full topic

item.title: C4D help
item.dc:creator: @exps35 exps35
item.description:
@exps35 wrote:

So you don’t even know where to download C4D, yet you are just going to open it up, model your guitar in it, and then go major in graphics (which is a very general statement) all in a matter of 3 months?

Good luck with it. I’m sure if you keep progressing and toying around with it, you can get good, but I don’t think computer generated graphics are in your near future. Maybe a year or two, but not 3 months.
Don’t get me wrong. Anything is possible…

On a side note… life isn’t always going to give you a ‘download knowledge here’ attitude. Learn to research what you’re getting into, and be persistent. Don’t give up because Maxon.com didn’t have a free c4d download on their main page.
